ProMED-mail wrote:
> [While anyone with a textbook can come up with a list of
> potential problems, has anyone hard data on what in fact
> occurs?
Well, this is from GIDEON:
Info: _Vibrio parahaemolyticus_ infection in Japan
The organism accounts for 45% to 60% of all food related infections.
Disease rates peak in August and September. Restaurants account for 40%.
4,063 outbreaks and 116,838 cases (5 fatal) were reported during 1980 to
1993 (including 100 outbreaks
and 3,124 cases in 1993). 224 incidents involving 5,849 cases were reported
in 1994; 245 incidents involving 5,515 cases in 1995.
Sure sounds like a major problem to me.
