Robin Lake (March 18th, Sushi note [2 mentions Steven Jay Gould's book on
Jewish Grandmothers. He may well have written one, but I suspect Lake is
referring to "New Guinea Tapeworms and Jewish Grandmothers", by Robert
Desowitz (Avon Books, 1981), a book I recommend highly to all the students in
my epidemiology of foodborne disease and zoonoses courses.
Being a bone fide member of the Writers Union of Canada I am also somewhat
touchy on the subject of properly attributed authorship.
